# {{project_name}} — Agent Guide

Tool-neutral operating manual for any agent CLI (Claude Code, Codex CLI, …)
working in this repo. Kubeharness-specific deterministic checks and the
deploy pipeline live in the `python -m harness` CLI; this file tells an
agent **when to use what**.

---

## Golden rules

1. **Never shell out to `kubectl`, `helm`, or `docker` directly.** Always go
   through `python -m harness <subcommand>`. The CLI owns timeouts, release
   naming, session logging, and uninstall-before-upgrade.
2. **Configuration is `config/harness.yaml`.** Never hardcode namespace,
   workspace path, release name, image tag, or arch in code or skills.
   Read the YAML at runtime.
3. **Workspace writes only.** Code and artifacts go in `{{workspace_dir}}/`.
   `harness/`, `.claude/`, `config/`, `context/`, `docs/` are off-limits —
   the hook will block writes regardless.
4. **One `/deploy` = one session log.** Every CLI invocation inside a
   deploy cycle appends to `$HARNESS_SESSION_LOG`. Do not create ad-hoc
   logs; they fragment the audit trail.
5. **LLM stays out of the CLI.** No API calls from Python. LLM judgment
   belongs to the main agent session and the two subagents below.

---

## Skills — load only when relevant

Skills are reference documents; `Read` a skill when starting a matching
task, forget it when done. Do **not** copy skill content into this file.

| Situation | Skill |
|---|---|
| Writing / editing Helm charts (`Chart.yaml`, `values*.yaml`, `templates/**`) | `.claude/skills/helm-chart-author/SKILL.md` |
| Writing / editing a `Dockerfile` | `.claude/skills/docker-author/SKILL.md` |
| Extracting a sub_goal spec from `context/phases/<phase>.md` | `.claude/skills/phase-spec-reader/SKILL.md` |
| Filling `values-dev.yaml` / `values-prod.yaml` from env matrix | `.claude/skills/cluster-env-inject/SKILL.md` |
| Diagnosing a runtime failure (usually invoked by `runtime-diagnoser`) | `.claude/skills/runtime-diagnosis/SKILL.md` |

---

## Subagents — when to call

- **`deploy-orchestrator`** — the only way to run a full deploy cycle.
  Invoked by `/deploy <phase> <sub_goal>`. Owns the verify-static →
  apply → verify-runtime loop with a retry budget. Applies diagnoser
  proposals directly — the `guard-path` hook enforces path policy, and
  every tool call is recorded to the session log for audit. Resolves
  `service_name` from `context/phases/<phase>.md` → `## Sub-goal: <sub_goal>`,
  so phase docs must exist before running.
- **`runtime-diagnoser`** — read-only Kubernetes diagnosis. Call via
  `Task(subagent_type="runtime-diagnoser", prompt=...)` when:
  - the user asks something like *"why is prometheus flaky?"*, or
  - `deploy-orchestrator` detects a `verify-runtime` failure.

Never call them from each other except in the documented direction
(orchestrator → diagnoser).

---

## Workflows

### New sub_goal from scratch

1. Load `phase-spec-reader`, read the sub_goal section in
   `context/phases/<phase>.md`, note the `**artifacts**:` field.
2. Load `helm-chart-author` / `docker-author` / `cluster-env-inject` as
   the artifacts dictate.
3. Write `{{workspace_dir}}/helm/<service>/` and/or
   `{{workspace_dir}}/docker/<service>/`. Writes land immediately —
   `guard-path` blocks any path outside the workspace, and each
   Write/Edit is appended to the active session log by the
   `log-tool-call` hook.
4. Confirm with the user, then suggest `/deploy <phase> <sub_goal>`.

### Iterate on an existing service

1. Load the relevant author skill.
2. Edit files under `{{workspace_dir}}/`.
3. Run `/deploy <phase> <sub_goal>` (or
   `python -m harness verify-static --service <svc>` if only static
   checks are in doubt).

### Observe only

User asks *"why is X misbehaving?"* → call `runtime-diagnoser` with
`service` + `failed_stage: observe`. Do **not** modify files based on
the response without explicit user instruction.

